Subject: Re: [T2] Need Alternator Tightning Bolt

On 3/8/06 9:53 PM, "Access Systems" <accessys(-at-)smart.net> wrote:

>> Can I get a bolt at say a hardware store that will do
>> the trick and stay put? Any ideas? If so what should I
>> look for?
> 
> get a fine thread minimum grade three (5 is better) bolt the right size,
> use a big enough washer (both sides) and pull her down real tight.
>

The screw you need is m8. I don't have my parts book at the moment, but the
length is about 30mm. An m8 x 30 allen socket cap screw will work perfectly.

Something like this:

http://www.boltdepot.com/product.aspx?cc=25&cs=132&cm=77&cd=1607

Hardness of metric fasteners is different than SAE. Most fasteners on a VW
(including this one) are grade 8.8.



